Debounce is a technique used to limit the rate at which a function is executed. When a function is debounced, it is delayed and only executed after a specified period of inactivity. This is useful in scenarios like handling user input events (e.g., typing in a search bar) to prevent excessive function calls, which can strain performance. Now, write a debounce function, which accepts "function" and "delay" as a parameter.

```
// Without debounce
const handleSearch = () => {
  // Make API call for search results
  fetchSearchResults();
};

// With debounce
const debouncedSearch = debounce(handleSearch, 300);

// In a search input
searchInput.addEventListener('input', debouncedSearch);
// Now the search will only happen after 300ms of inactivity
// If the user types quickly, the function won't be called for each keystroke
